content: First of all, Merry Christmas to you!!
on January 4, the ex-world champion Norihiko Kawamura will teach us a lesson.
It is your unique opportunity to learn
We hope that more VIP teachers will teach us in coming year.
Those VIP lessons usually will take place on Sunday
And now, let us begin, with the participation check,
casar, dhalsim, bergamot, yun_shou, sosei, weigui, luwenzhe, shuwang, mayhem, fallnavy, yzhnie, Intotherenju, ZenoaWilu, virag, killer21st, pengyu, Ikon, yyfcsd, coco_yuang.
Today, we will analyse a very interesting game together.
And you will have a chance to see the development of a good renju master,
and we can all study and learn from it.
The master we will study about today is Chen Shoude. :)
And the game we will study today was played about 40 minutes ago.
i saw the whole match,that's great!
Chen was black, and I was white.
For my suprise, he showed a very powerful opening development,
which I did not know of before.
It has been quite popular in recent years.
so nice to see you here!
Nice to meet you, Mr Kawamura
Today I want to learn this system.
You can look at our lesson
and if any question, you can always ask.
The popular 9th moves that I have seen
but they dont bring much success for blacks
at first, I didnt think its possible move
I thought, it must be white win or something.
this 9 is populer in China Net games now:)
I was thinking of this active 10th move,
now, not including yy, who can tel black next move?
you have all understood the main point - black must be active
lets have one participation check now
and i will allow virag to show his idea

i began to worry a little
here, another difficult moment for me..
finally, i chose this move, as i could not see the black win after that.
if 12-g10, I think there is a vct for black

Now, lets go back to the game.
Lets see how yyfcsd continued here.
then the stone 13 will help the blacks to win
because all white's counter-attack is dead.
By the 17th move, the position had calmed down
it looks like some usual peaceful opening
I was short of time by then,
how much did i have time, yy you remember?
about 2 mins of main time, and 1 minute of bayomi time
This series of moves was in favor of whites.
Now comes out the weakness of the 23rd move.
the line 10_24 is too good for white now
it was better for black to not use the e11 point,
and then just block it if white takes e11
and even though after that blocking white would have two more open lines left,
they are too far from lower side
I regret when I put it
its not always easy to play optimal moves.
Then, I realized, if I look for left side win for too long, i will lose by time soon.
So I just stopped looking at the left side for a moment,
and played a move to the right.
And while now he was thinking about 37th move,
I was looking what is really happening on the left.
Therefore, he played a four first,
he can see the danger so fast
I already run in the bayomi time...
Ando is a great time manager!
I thought maybe you cannot find a win so quickily
what if he used another defense.
that is what we can check together now.
now, who would like to try white attack
if both of us have 5 minutes left, I will take this 41
this 41 has both advantage and disadvantage
the adv is - its closer to whites
the disadv - no counter-attack VCF threat for blacks later
hmm,give up.this 43 is surprise to me:)
